22    /**
23    * Context for the process of deserialization a single root-level value.
24    * Used to allow passing in configuration settings and reusable temporary
25    * objects (scrap arrays, containers).
26    *<p>
27    * Instance life-cycle is such that an partially configured "blueprint" object
28    * is registered with {@link ObjectMapper} (and {@link ObjectReader},
29    * and when an actual instance is needed for deserialization,
30    * a fully configured instance will
31    * be created using a method in excented API of sub-class
32    * ({@link com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.DefaultDeserializationContext#createInstance}).
33    * Each instance is guaranteed to only be used from single-threaded context;
34    * instances may be reused iff no configuration has changed.
35    *<p>
36    * Defined as abstract class so that implementations must define methods
37    * for reconfiguring blueprints and creating instances.
38    */
